WEBVTT

00:00.125 --> 00:01.834
[Brian] Previously on
What About Brian:

00:01.834 --> 00:04.500
[Bridget] I thought if you knew
about me and your father

00:04.500 --> 00:07.500
that you would never see
me in a romantic way again.

00:07.500 --> 00:09.166
You're right, I won't.

00:09.166 --> 00:10.875
- My name is T.K.
- Deena.

00:10.875 --> 00:13.542
I want to ask you in,
it's just that my husband...

00:13.542 --> 00:16.208
...ex is in there.

00:18.000 --> 00:20.709
- I can take care of myself.
- Oh, you think so?

00:28.333 --> 00:31.917
[♪ Ben Lee: Close As I've Come]

00:31.917 --> 00:34.208
[machine beeps]

00:34.208 --> 00:36.583
Brian, it's your Dad.

00:36.583 --> 00:39.291
You said I never call you
so I'm calling you.

00:39.291 --> 00:42.959
I hope we can talk
about Bridget and everything.

00:42.959 --> 00:47.083
I'd really like to do it before
Monday, so, uh, please give me
a call.

00:47.083 --> 00:48.166
[machine beeps]

00:48.166 --> 00:50.709
♪ I slipped into a house ♪

00:50.709 --> 00:55.041
♪ To escape my enemies ♪

00:55.041 --> 00:59.291
♪ And opened the door
to another world ♪

01:01.583 --> 01:05.083
♪ But I love you more ♪

01:05.083 --> 01:08.417
♪ Than any of them ♪

01:08.417 --> 01:11.500
♪ And ever before ♪

01:11.500 --> 01:15.542
♪ Look how close I've come
How close I've come ♪

01:15.542 --> 01:18.875
♪ How close I've come
How close I've come ♪

01:18.875 --> 01:22.583
♪ Look how close I've come
I'm far away ♪

01:24.959 --> 01:28.375
I swear, if this baby
doesn't come soon,
I'm gonna lose my mind.

01:28.375 --> 01:30.417
The last few weeks
are the worst.

01:30.417 --> 01:33.583
Weeks? Do not say weeks.
It better be days.

01:33.583 --> 01:35.625
This kid clearly hates me.

01:35.625 --> 01:38.250
She won't let me eat,
she's constantly kicking.

01:38.250 --> 01:40.917
And I don't mean "I just
felt the baby kick" kick,

01:40.917 --> 01:43.291
I mean full-on
Sydney Bristow kicks.

01:43.291 --> 01:46.125
I'm bloated. I can't sleep.

01:46.125 --> 01:49.959
Not to mention the peeing
and the hemorrhoids and the
stretch marks

01:49.959 --> 01:52.792
and those nauseatingly
sympathetic stares...

01:54.834 --> 01:57.583
Oh, God, I'm doing it.
I'm sorry.

01:57.583 --> 02:01.250
I am so...
I am so never having a baby.

02:01.250 --> 02:04.291
There are things you can do
to bring the labor on.

02:04.291 --> 02:08.333
Oh, yeah. I heard about
a salad dressing at a restaurant
by the ocean

02:08.333 --> 02:11.458
- that can start
your contractions.
- Oh, right.

02:11.458 --> 02:15.041
- And hiking uphill,
my sister said.
- Oh, yeah.

02:15.041 --> 02:19.166
Hiking, dumbbell squats,
swinging on the swings
at the playground...

02:19.166 --> 02:23.458
Let's go. I'll swing on a swing
while eating a salad and lifting
weights.

02:23.458 --> 02:26.083
Speaking of which,
dinner's ready.

02:26.083 --> 02:28.625
Would it kill the guys
to help us?

02:28.625 --> 02:31.667
- It's a perfectly
beautiful thing.
- Like you're there.

02:31.667 --> 02:34.208
Better. You don't spend
ten dollars for a beer.

02:34.208 --> 02:35.792
Do that thing
with the windows.

02:37.125 --> 02:38.709
[all] Oh!

02:38.709 --> 02:41.208
Guys? Food's ready.

02:42.917 --> 02:45.083
- Guys!
- [all] Hey!

02:45.083 --> 02:47.834
Dinner!

02:47.834 --> 02:50.750
- Why'd you marry her?
- The $64,000 question.

02:50.750 --> 02:52.458
Because I look good in makeup.

02:52.458 --> 02:54.375
- You guys ready for court?
- Jimmy.

02:54.375 --> 02:57.291
It's my first day with the
plasma. Don't kill my buzz.

02:57.291 --> 03:00.250
I won't. Long as you guys
keep mouths shut, act sorry.

03:00.250 --> 03:03.333
Worse case, the judge sentences
you to community service.

03:03.333 --> 03:07.583
- Can't believe we have to
go to court for a fight.
- If Ivy didn't call the cops.

03:07.583 --> 03:09.667
If Adam could hold his liquor...

03:09.667 --> 03:13.041
If you all could be quiet,
I could get my food and go
watch the game.

03:13.041 --> 03:14.542
- Amen to that.
- Look at this.

03:14.542 --> 03:17.500
- [Adam] Mm-hmm.
- [cell phone rings]

03:21.125 --> 03:25.500
- Who was that?
- Oh, it was, um... T.K.

03:25.500 --> 03:27.417
So why didn't you answer it?

03:27.417 --> 03:31.041
I don't know. It's a little
weird. Dave's in the next room.

03:31.041 --> 03:33.208
Deena, you and Dave
are separated.

03:33.208 --> 03:36.583
It is perfectly acceptable for
you to date. We discussed this.

03:36.583 --> 03:39.041
Yeah, I know we did.

03:39.041 --> 03:42.458
It's just... I think
it's a little soon.

03:42.458 --> 03:45.709
- I barely know
the guy, you know?
- You need to get to know him.

03:45.709 --> 03:48.625
- That's why you
should call him back.
- Call who back?

03:48.625 --> 03:52.667
- Oh, no, it's just
a... cupcake thing.
- Oh.

03:52.667 --> 03:54.959
- [Nicole] I am so hungry.
- Yeah, right?

03:54.959 --> 03:57.125
When you get as big
as a house, you know...

03:57.125 --> 04:00.333
- So...
- Yeah. It happens.

04:00.333 --> 04:02.709
[chuckles]

04:02.709 --> 04:06.083
How come these people think
that we still can't be friends?

04:06.083 --> 04:08.208
I know.
They're so wrong, you know?

04:08.208 --> 04:11.875
I think it's great that
we can all... still hang out.

04:11.875 --> 04:14.083
- Yeah? Me, too.
- Yeah.

04:14.083 --> 04:17.625
My sandwiches. You didn't
put my sandwiches out.

04:17.625 --> 04:20.125
Oh, honey, um, your
sandwiches look horrible.

04:20.125 --> 04:22.125
Are you kidding me?
These are great!

04:22.125 --> 04:24.041
Yeah. Where did
you even get them?

04:24.041 --> 04:25.208
Work.

04:27.041 --> 04:29.583
Um... So I noticed that

04:29.583 --> 04:31.959
you're not wearing
your ring anymore.

04:31.959 --> 04:36.291
Yeah. I mean, I figured you're
not wearing yours either, so...

04:36.291 --> 04:38.041
Makes sense.

04:38.041 --> 04:41.417
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

04:42.542 --> 04:43.917
- So what's up?
- Nothing.

04:43.917 --> 04:46.750
Why do you look like
you're gonna murder
that lasagna?

04:46.750 --> 04:49.250
It's vegetarian.
It deserves to be killed.

04:51.583 --> 04:54.834
Is it the Dad and Bridget thing?

04:56.458 --> 04:57.792
Who told you?

04:57.792 --> 05:00.875
Adam told Dave,
Dave told Deena,
Deena told me.

05:02.083 --> 05:04.125
Well, yeah. It's just...

05:04.125 --> 05:06.959
I feel so let down
by him, and her.

05:06.959 --> 05:10.667
Brian, Dad is who he is.
He's never gonna change.

05:12.291 --> 05:14.625
I made my peace with that
a long time ago.

05:14.625 --> 05:16.959
- Well, I'm not
sure I can do that.
- Why not?

05:16.959 --> 05:20.000
He never does the right thing.
He's supposed to be the dad.

05:20.000 --> 05:22.208
He's not supposed to
date the girl I date.

05:22.208 --> 05:23.875
God, that sounds ridiculous.

05:23.875 --> 05:26.917
- Come on, let's watch the game.
- You hate basketball.

05:26.917 --> 05:30.834
Right now basketball and I
have a lot in common and
I need to sit. Come on.

05:30.834 --> 05:32.500
No, you go.

05:34.000 --> 05:37.166
Come on. Come on, hot stuff.
Sandwich, no?

05:37.166 --> 05:39.208
How about you?
You want a sandwich?

05:39.208 --> 05:41.458
What is with you
and sandwiches?

05:41.458 --> 05:45.500
They're awful. They have labels.
Who eats something called
"tofurella?"

05:45.500 --> 05:48.750
- What the hell is "tofurella?"
- Yummy goodness is what it is.

05:48.750 --> 05:51.750
There's this sweet sandwich lady
at work who sells them.

05:51.750 --> 05:54.458
I figured I'd help her out.
What is your problem?

05:54.458 --> 05:56.500
Why? You don't like a sandwich?

05:56.500 --> 05:57.917
[bell dings]

06:03.834 --> 06:07.083
I would eat her
sandwich any day.

06:07.083 --> 06:09.542
- You're disgusting.
- Whatever.

06:09.542 --> 06:11.333
You think you got
a shot with her?

06:11.333 --> 06:14.542
She is so out of
your league, Greco,

06:14.542 --> 06:18.083
it doesn't matter how
many sandwiches you buy.

06:18.083 --> 06:22.208
- Hey, how's my
favorite customer?
- Me? Good. You?

06:22.208 --> 06:25.250
- "Me, good, you."
Sound like a caveman.
- I'm good.

06:25.250 --> 06:27.917
- I brought you
a new one. A BLG.
- What's a BLG?

06:27.917 --> 06:31.542
Bacon, lettuce and grapes.
I was going for that whole
salty/sweet thing.

06:31.542 --> 06:34.500
Oh, well. Oh, yeah.
That's good.

06:34.500 --> 06:36.875
'Cause people are gonna
wanna have a taste.

06:36.875 --> 06:39.625
- Don't worry. I have plenty.
- That's great, cool.

06:39.625 --> 06:42.375
'Cause I had a big breakfast.
Waffles and syrup.

06:42.375 --> 06:44.125
Oh, OK.

06:44.125 --> 06:47.875
There was something that
I wanted to ask you and...

06:50.000 --> 06:52.208
You have any plain
ham and cheese?

06:52.208 --> 06:55.417
The damage was minimal, the
injuries to all parties minor,

06:55.417 --> 06:58.709
and due to the emotional duress
both defendants were under,

06:58.709 --> 07:01.458
- I ask the court's leniency.
- Thank you. [snorts]

07:01.458 --> 07:03.000
After reviewing the facts,

07:03.000 --> 07:06.333
I think it's appropriate for
your clients to perform 50 hours

07:06.333 --> 07:09.500
of community service
in the next four weeks.

07:09.500 --> 07:11.083
- Fifty hours?
- Shh!

07:11.083 --> 07:14.208
What was that, Mr... Davis?

07:14.208 --> 07:18.375
Nothing. Nothing, Your Honor.
He does that sometimes.
Blurts things out.

07:18.375 --> 07:21.583
- I'd like to hear
from Mr. Davis.
- Oh, this is gonna be bad.

07:21.583 --> 07:23.417
Uh... [clears throat]

07:24.458 --> 07:26.583
We paid for the damages,
Your Honor.

07:26.583 --> 07:29.083
No one was hurt.
It was just a dumb bar fight.

07:29.083 --> 07:32.834
Fifty does seem... excessive.

07:34.625 --> 07:38.208
And what do you feel would be
more appropriate? [snorts]

07:38.208 --> 07:42.625
What do your years of legal
expertise suggest, Mr. Davis?

07:44.125 --> 07:45.208
Uh...

07:46.959 --> 07:49.417
Fifty. Fifty sounds great.

07:49.417 --> 07:54.041
Really. I'm interested to hear
your thoughts. [snorts]

07:54.041 --> 07:57.959
Well, with all due respect,
Your Honor, I'd say around...

08:00.959 --> 08:03.417
...thirty?
That seems fair to me.

08:06.125 --> 08:08.834
Well, then, thirty it is.

08:08.834 --> 08:11.583
OK then, we have a deal on the
table.

08:11.583 --> 08:14.583
- Four weeks to do 30 hours.
- Nice try, counselor.

08:14.583 --> 08:17.792
I'm gonna grant your request
for 30 hours of service.

08:17.792 --> 08:20.166
- To be completed in four days.
- What?

08:20.166 --> 08:24.542
- Well, that's impossible.
- You fail to do that,
I'll double it.

08:24.542 --> 08:27.208
Now get out of here.

08:27.208 --> 08:30.166
- [Jimmy] I told you
not to talk.
- He kept asking questions.

08:30.166 --> 08:32.875
He was making sounds with his
nose. He threw me off my game.

08:32.875 --> 08:35.750
I can't do 30 hours.
I have the Jensen case.

08:35.750 --> 08:39.792
- Rossoff assigned it to me.
I can't screw this up.
- You can do an overnight.

08:39.792 --> 08:41.959
You can spend the
whole night at a shelter.

08:41.959 --> 08:45.750
Counts triple time.
Ten hours times three.
You're done, didn't miss work.

08:45.750 --> 08:47.792
- I don't mind missing work.
- Shut up.

08:47.792 --> 08:49.583
- What?
- Just don't talk.

08:49.583 --> 08:52.709
Your big mouth has screwed up
enough for one day already.

08:52.709 --> 08:54.333
[♪ Low Stars:
Calling All Friends]

08:54.333 --> 08:59.667
♪ Calling all friends and
people I met on the way down ♪

08:59.667 --> 09:04.208
♪ Calling all friends
and people I don't even know ♪

09:05.625 --> 09:07.208
♪ Calling on high ♪

09:07.208 --> 09:10.166
♪ I want to believe
there's a way now ♪

09:12.291 --> 09:17.125
♪ I'm too tired to pretend
I don't want to be alone ♪

09:17.125 --> 09:20.208
♪ I'm calling all friends ♪♪

09:25.667 --> 09:28.375
She was great.
She was happy to talk to me.

09:28.375 --> 09:31.792
So happy she used her
frequent flyer miles to
get a ticket to LA.

09:31.792 --> 09:33.875
- Oh, no.
- Oh, yes.

09:33.875 --> 09:37.875
Mom doesn't do anything halfway.
She'll be here Thursday for the
weekend.

09:37.875 --> 09:40.875
- Thought I'd see her
after work. If you wanted...
- No!

09:40.875 --> 09:43.583
- Nic!
- I have a written
excuse from my doctor.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.583
Stress is not good for the baby.

09:45.583 --> 09:49.458
Then why are you running,
looking like you're about
to have a heart attack?

09:49.458 --> 09:52.083
Ivy said that running uphill
could bring on labor.

09:52.083 --> 09:54.250
Come with me.
She wants to see you.

09:54.250 --> 09:57.750
My relationship with Mom
makes you and Dad look like
best friends.

09:57.750 --> 10:01.834
I have my own mother issues
right now. Like when am I
gonna finally become one?

10:04.041 --> 10:08.750
- I'm sorry. I can't.
- I gotta get to work.

10:12.917 --> 10:15.917
Brian. Can we talk, please?

10:15.917 --> 10:18.333
About business? Sure.

10:18.333 --> 10:21.917
Seriously, I want to have an
actual discussion with you, OK?

10:21.917 --> 10:23.166
- Hold it.
- I've been...

10:27.125 --> 10:31.125
Morning. Everybody OK?

10:31.125 --> 10:34.125
Let's see. I'm stuck in
the elevator with you two.

10:34.125 --> 10:37.125
I have to leave work early
so I can spend the night at some

10:37.125 --> 10:40.625
church homeless shelter.
Mom's coming in town
to see me and Nic,

10:40.625 --> 10:44.208
only Nic doesn't wanna see her
so I get to do it all by myself,
again.

10:44.208 --> 10:49.083
Yeah, all in all,
everything's pretty great.

10:49.083 --> 10:53.250
- Did you hear what
I said about Mom, Dad?
- Yeah.

10:53.250 --> 10:56.125
You don't care
how she is, or anything?

10:56.125 --> 10:58.291
How is she?

10:58.291 --> 11:01.959
When she leaves you a message,
do you return her calls?

11:01.959 --> 11:03.625
[bell dings]

11:04.959 --> 11:08.667
- Brian, this is only three.
- I knew that.

11:11.166 --> 11:13.291
- So I called T.K.
- Good for you.

11:13.291 --> 11:16.959
- We're going to dinner.
- Good. When?

11:16.959 --> 11:21.166
- Tonight.
- [sighs] You go, girl.

11:21.166 --> 11:24.667
It works out great because
Dave has the girls every other
Tuesday,

11:24.667 --> 11:27.583
and tonight's Tuesday, so...

11:30.125 --> 11:33.333
- This is good, right?
- Yeah. I mean,
it's just dinner.

11:33.333 --> 11:35.875
Worst case scenario,
you have no connection.

11:35.875 --> 11:38.375
You skip dessert
and you're home in two hours.

11:38.375 --> 11:42.000
- Yeah.
- OK. Thanks.

11:42.000 --> 11:44.375
So what do you think
they have in this stuff?

11:44.375 --> 11:47.875
A lot of oil,
some mustard and anchovy bits.

11:47.875 --> 11:51.834
- OK, well, here goes.
- No!

11:51.834 --> 11:54.709
Honey, you're not
supposed to drink it!

11:54.709 --> 11:57.542
Oh! Maybe it'll work faster.

11:57.542 --> 12:00.875
The firm wants you to
settle this out of court.
Quietly. No PR.

12:00.875 --> 12:02.542
How high are we willing to go?

12:02.542 --> 12:05.291
Jensen'll go up to three
million. No more than that.

12:05.291 --> 12:07.750
Jimmy, I'll be fine.

12:07.750 --> 12:10.542
Gentlemen, thank you for coming.
I'm Adam Hillman.

12:10.542 --> 12:12.500
- Simon Coleman.
- Hi.

12:12.500 --> 12:16.750
I am sorry about your father.
I can't imagine what you must
be experiencing.

12:16.750 --> 12:19.375
Yes, well, Mr. Miller's ordeal

12:19.375 --> 12:23.375
has been, and continues to be,
uh, quite formidable.

12:23.375 --> 12:26.583
Well, after a careful review
of the files here, it seems...

12:26.583 --> 12:28.458
My dad was a pretty healthy guy.

12:28.458 --> 12:31.875
But after the accident
at the factory...

12:33.417 --> 12:35.417
He hasn't walked in over a year.

12:36.750 --> 12:40.250
Workers comp won't pay
because the company is saying

12:40.250 --> 12:43.250
that it was operator error.

12:43.250 --> 12:47.583
Bills are huge.
I just need a little help.

12:47.583 --> 12:50.250
Well, moving right along...

12:50.250 --> 12:54.333
With the past expenditures
and future costs,

12:54.333 --> 12:59.417
we are not prepared to accept
anything less than, um...

13:14.083 --> 13:15.458
That's quite a number.

13:17.041 --> 13:19.792
I'm gonna have to
discuss it with my client.

13:19.792 --> 13:22.333
So let's see what I can do.

13:24.291 --> 13:26.458
Is it me or is she
staring at me right now?

13:26.458 --> 13:28.792
It's like everywhere I go,
there she is.

13:28.792 --> 13:31.458
Maybe you should ask her
to the Berry Festival.

13:31.458 --> 13:34.417
- Fine. Mock if you will.
- Oh, I will.

13:36.125 --> 13:37.208
Oh, wow.

13:43.166 --> 13:45.458
That's the sweet
little sandwich lady?

13:45.458 --> 13:48.625
- Girl. We call her
"Sandwich Girl."
- You gonna ask her out?

13:48.625 --> 13:51.125
- Why? Should I?
- Dave, she waved. She smiled.

13:51.125 --> 13:54.500
It's called flirting, look into
it. What are you waiting for?

13:54.500 --> 13:57.333
Don't you think she's
a little out of my league?

13:57.333 --> 13:59.792
- Maybe. But so's Deena.
- You're hilarious.

13:59.792 --> 14:02.000
You just need to exude
confidence. Go.

14:02.000 --> 14:04.834
- Do it. Come on. Go!
- Oh, fine.

14:08.333 --> 14:09.375
Go get 'em, tiger.

14:09.375 --> 14:13.250
[music plays]

14:31.959 --> 14:37.375
How do you like that, Hank?
Oh, yeah. El Greco's back!

14:37.375 --> 14:39.041
- Nice!
- It's on for tonight.

14:39.041 --> 14:42.125
[Deena] Dave, tonight is
the other Tuesday and I have
a date, too.

14:42.125 --> 14:46.875
OK, so, uh, what can we do?

14:46.875 --> 14:49.667
Why is there an elephant
swinging on our swing set?

14:49.667 --> 14:53.208
No, that's just Nicole.
She's trying to force labor.

14:53.208 --> 14:54.750
- [Dave] In our yard?
- Yeah.

14:57.250 --> 14:59.500
What do you think
if we just got a sitter?

14:59.500 --> 15:02.458
I mean, if we were married
and we were going out,

15:02.458 --> 15:06.000
- we would have to
get Maria anyway.
- So that... Let's do that.

15:06.000 --> 15:07.834
- Great.
- Great.

15:07.834 --> 15:09.750
- One more question.
- Yeah?

15:09.750 --> 15:11.208
Um...

15:11.208 --> 15:14.208
I... I'm not exactly
sure what to do.

15:14.208 --> 15:17.417
- And I wanted to ask your help.
- What are you talking about?

15:17.417 --> 15:19.333
On a date. Don't know
what people do.

15:19.333 --> 15:23.583
I know it's a little weird,
me asking you for advice.

15:23.583 --> 15:27.083
- A little.
- I figured, you're a woman,

15:27.083 --> 15:29.750
and nobody knows me better
than you, right?

15:29.750 --> 15:33.709
- So I thought
maybe you could...
- I don't know. Um...

15:35.417 --> 15:38.750
Just be yourself.
Keep it simple.

15:38.750 --> 15:42.208
Girls don't really like it
when guys do a lot of crazy
stuff.

15:42.208 --> 15:45.625
Great. Simple. Simple.
I can do simple, right?

15:45.625 --> 15:47.917
- Nobody simpler than me.
- That's right.

15:47.917 --> 15:51.583
- That's great.
Thanks, honey. Really.
- Yeah, OK.

15:51.583 --> 15:56.917
- Oh, and hey, have a good date.
- I will. You, too.

15:59.667 --> 16:01.917
[groans]

16:01.917 --> 16:04.792
- Was that Dave?
- Yes, and guess what?

16:04.792 --> 16:06.792
- What?
